    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<ol>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5818373/does-the-jpa-specification-allow-references-to-non-primary-key-columns\">JPA does not allow references to non-PK columns</a>.</p></li>\n<li><p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/11245823/685962\">ReferencedColumn property is used to specify join column, when there is a composite PK in referenced table</a>.</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>How can I make this work??</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Normalize your database to use common PK-FK relationships. If needed - define composite PK.</p>\n"
